 The man was speeding to hospital after a drowning incident at home. While rushing to hospital in his Mustang, the man allegedly skipped a red light, causing the multiple vehicle collision.
One of the victims in another vehicle was seriously injured, while the driver of another vehicle hit a tree head-on. The accident occurred in the intersection of Walter Sisulu and Clubville’s Van der Merwe Street.
It happened a block away from the banquet hall where more than 700 wrestlers were competing in a cross country competition. • Get your copy of the Middelburg Observer this week for the full details of what happened.     Nuwe tierbaba by Mbidi Video: Opruimingswerk begin na drie damwalle breek weens wolkbreuk Annica van Staden slagoffers verloor duisende VIDEO: Seekoei kuier op Elandslaagte Stoor ons bystand nommer (072 248 3855) en stuur ons ‘n Whatsapp boodskap met die woorde “Add me” om deel te word van ons uitsaailys. “Like” ons op Facebook, of volg ons op Twitter en Instagram. Volg ons YouTube kanaal. Kliek op die skakel om te registreer om ons nuusbrief met die jongste nuus per e-pos te kry Kontak die redaksie op ons 24 uur bystandnommer 072 248 3855, of stuur ‘n e-pos aan ons redakteur tobie@mobserver.co.za 